cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.NE, cs.SE 

This paper focuses on the performance limits of Apache Spark for machine learning applications, which involves distributed computing and optimization techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the characteristics and optimization of machine learning algorithms, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with large datasets and their implications, which is relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the trade-off between computation time and communication latency, which is relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper proposes practical techniques to alleviate overheads, which is relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
